radiographic_examinations.findings: Abnormal appearance of the appendix with an appendicular at the base of the appendix; the appendix is dilated up to 14 mm with stones in the lumen; periappendiceal fat stranding without definite signs of perforation; no abscess seen; loops of small bowel demonstrate no signs of ileus or obstruction; no retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy; trace free fluid could be physiologic.
